    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g] </span><strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>and <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>peri-peri paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
