    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>peri peri paste </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>,<strong> </strong>mix everything together and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> [340ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly thickened</p>",
