    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spring greens </strong>then pat them dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> with a splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p>",
